Skip demo clients whose dependencies are missing, instead of failing the build.

-Ddemo-clients is all-or-nothing, and one entry in the list -- the text editor
-- wants pangocairo, which Tunix does not have. Upstream turns that into a hard
error, so a single unported dependency costs every other demo: flower, smoke,
image, clickdot, resizor, stacking, dnd and the rest, all of which need nothing
beyond the toy toolkit that is already here.

Skipping the ones that cannot be built, with a warning naming what they wanted,
keeps the rest and makes the set self-adjusting: port pango later and the editor
starts building with no change here.

--- a/clients/meson.build
+++ b/clients/meson.build
@@ -344,14 +344,21 @@
 		t_name = 'weston-' + t.get('basename')
 		t_srcs = [ t.get('basename') + '.c' ] + t.get('add_sources', [])
 		t_deps = [ dep_toytoolkit, t.get('dep_objs', []) ]
+		t_skip = false
 		foreach depname : t.get('deps', [])
 			dep = dependency(depname, required: false)
 			if not dep.found()
-				error('@0@ requires \'@1@\' which was not found. If you rather not build this, set \'-Ddemo-clients=false\'.'.format(t_name, depname))
+				warning('@0@ requires \'@1@\' which was not found; skipping it.'.format(t_name, depname))
+				t_skip = true
+				break
 			endif
 			t_deps += dep
 		endforeach
 
+		if t_skip
+			continue
+		endif
+
 		executable(
 			t_name, t_srcs,
 			include_directories: common_inc,
